snippet.textDisplay: Ngl while I think this is a good way to look at stuff when you get robbed, I think there's a huge difference between choosing to get rid of stuff, and having stuff forcefully taken from you. One situation is much more of a violation than the other, and often it isn't what's taken that bothers you, but that it was taken without your consent by someone who entered your home uninvited and unseen. You lost more items by purposefully getting rid of them, but it was entirely your choice and within your control, whereas Marzia didn't have a choice or control over what happened to her things. Even if nothing had been taken the invasion itself is unsettling for most. It's an interesting topic though for sure, and I imagine for many people who have been robbed that reasoning through it like this helps to deal with it.
